  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a cast silver medal depicting Jan Hus (c. 1369/1370–1415), the Czech religious reformer who was burned at the stake as a heretic at the Council of Constance on 6 July 1415. The obverse shows Hus's portrait bust; the reverse depicts his execution with Latin inscriptions including his famous prophecy. The medal belongs to the well-documented \"Hustaler\" tradition of Reformation commemorative medals. Despite the \"1415\" date inscribed on the medal, it was **not manufactured in 1415** — it is a later commemorative piece, most likely from the early 18th century (c. 1700–1740). It was part of the personal collection of Pieter Teyler van der Hulst, the museum's founder.",
      "classified_as": [
        {
          "id": "http://vocab.getty.edu/aat/300411780",
          "_label": "description"
        }
